name: Cope
reason: The pioneer of 'Copy Trading' scoring on Solana. Users staked COPE to rank traders. The project suffered from internal team friction, resulting in a high historical insider score and legacy baggage.

name: Rope
reason: One of the first 'Meme-Fi' experiments, originally designed as a volatility index. It defines the 'Class E' archetype by blending ironic meme culture with complex financial mechanics.

name: BonkEarn
reason: A showcase for the Solana Token-2022 standard. Implements protocol-level transfer taxes and burns to generate yield for holders. Highly experimental technical implementation.

name: Bozo Hybrid
reason: Pioneered the 'Hybrid' meta, functioning simultaneously as a fungible token and a claim on NFTs. Innovative structure that blurs the lines between SPL tokens and Metaplex standards.

name: Grape Network
reason: The standard for token-gated communities on Discord. Essential infrastructure for DAOs, though its token economics have struggled to capture value commensurate with its utility.

name: SolMail
reason: An attempt to create an on-chain email standard. Functionality is novel, but the long-term viability of paying for individual messages remains an experimental economic model.

name: Analos
reason: A narrative-driven meme coin ('Solana' spelled backwards). Represents the 'mirror' meta. High volatility and rapid capital rotation typical of short-lived narrative plays.

name: Only1
reason: A decentralized social platform similar to Patreon. Users buy NFTs to stake on creators. Moderate insider score due to VC backing and platform development centralization.

name: Samoyedcoin
reason: The original Solana dog coin. Unlike newer memes, its supply is well-distributed over years, resulting in a very low insider score and 'blue-chip' meme status.

name: Blockasset
reason: Sports athlete tokenization platform. Partnerships with major athletes create value, but the model relies heavily on centralized partnerships and team execution.
